'What are you doing with these people? These are my people,' he told the Nazi guards, who let them go after Schindler offered further bribes.

Leyon didn't talk about his wartime experiences until 1993 and Steven Spielberg's acclaimed film Schindler's List prompted him to share his story.

He went on to take part in an educational program where Holocaust survivors spoke in high schools and college campuses providing a personal testimony of the horrors committed by Hitler's Nazi party.

