He often told stories of his beloved brother Tsalig, who at 16, chose to go to a death camp with his girlfriend rather than accept Schindler's offer to save him - he didn't want her to be alone.

The young couple was murdered.

Leyson once met Schindler in the U.S. many years on and found that he still remembered him.  

'I know who you are. You are little Leyson!,' he said.

Leyson worked as a teacher at Huntington Park High School, Los Angeles for 39 years.

He lived in Fullerton with his wife, Liz, and had two children.

